---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

import ContactCTA from "../components/ContactCTA.astro";
import Hero from "../components/Hero.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
	title="About | Raphaël Pellure"
	description="About Raphaël Pellure — Image processing, computer vision & embedded systems engineer from ENSEEIHT."
>
	<div class="stack gap-20">
		<main class="wrapper about">
			<Hero
				title="About"
				tagline="Thanks for stopping by. Read below to learn more about myself and my background."
			>
				<img
					width="1553"
					height="873"
					src="/assets/at-work.jpg"
					alt="Raphaël Pellure working on image processing and computer vision projects"
				/>
			</Hero>

			<section>
				<h2 class="section-title">Background</h2>
				<div class="content">
					<p>
						I'm an engineering student specializing in <strong
							>Signal, Image & AI (IATI – SIA)</strong
						> at <strong>ENSEEIHT</strong> (Toulouse). My interests sit
						at the intersection of <strong>image processing</strong
						>, <strong>computer vision</strong>, and <strong
							>embedded systems</strong
						>, with applications spanning <em>cinema/VFX</em>, <em
							>aerospace & drones</em
						>, and <em>scientific imaging</em>.
					</p>
					<br />
					<p>
						Recently, I completed a 2‑month internship with the <strong
							>STORM team (IRIT Toulouse)</strong
						> on <em>Painty</em>, a C++ application for hand‑painted
						animation inbetweening. Before that, I worked on a
						MATLAB project <em
							>“MAT: Medial Axis Extraction and 3D Meshing”</em
						> (multi‑view reconstruction with SLIC segmentation, skeleton
						extraction, and surface meshing) and a C/OpenCV project on
						<strong>texture image segmentation</strong>
						(K‑means & Mean‑Shift, metrics & visualization tools).
					</p>
					<p>
						On the embedded/low‑level side, I’ve built FPGA and DSP
						skills (VHDL on Artix‑7, SHARC DSP assembly).
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="section-title">Education</h2>
				<div class="content">
					<p>
						<strong>ENSEEIHT – Toulouse, France</strong> — IATI (SIA),
						last year in progress.<br />
						Focus: Applied mathematics, advanced signal & image processing,
						information theory, optimization under constraints, architectures
						& synchronous digital design, FPGA technology, DSP, multivariate
						analysis, inverse problems, introduction to deep learning,
						advanced statistics & computational statistics.
					</p>
					<br />
					<p>
						<strong>University of Birmingham (UK)</strong> — Exchange
						semester.<br />
						Modules: <em>Data Mining & Machine Learning</em> (text IR,
						HMMs, ASR), <em>Small Embedded Systems</em> (industrial embedded
						design, digital & analog circuits, C programming), <em
							>Electronic Engineering</em
						>.
					</p>
					<br />
					<p>
						<strong>Camille Jullian – Bordeaux, France</strong> — CPGE
						(MPSI/MP).<br />
						Focus : advanced mathematics, physics, and computer science
						foundations, including linear algebra, differential equations,
						probability/statistics, and algorithmic problem-solving.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="section-title">Associative & cultural involvement</h2>
				<div class="content">
					<p>
						<strong>TVn7</strong> — Video editing.<br />
						<strong>Photo7</strong> — Photography.<br />
						<strong>ABC Toulouse</strong> — Cinema programming.<br />
						<strong>Interests</strong>: photography, cinema, rock culture, sports.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>


			<section>
	<h2 class="section-title">Skills</h2>
	<div class="content">
		<ul class="skills-list">
			<li><strong>Programming:</strong> Python (NumPy, OpenCV, PyTorch, TensorFlow), C/C++, MATLAB, VHDL, DSP Assembly</li>
			<li><strong>Tools & Frameworks:</strong> VsCode, Visual Studio, Qt, Git, Blender (4.5), Photoshop, Premiere Pro</li>
			<li><strong>Languages:</strong> French (native), English (C1), Spanish (B2)</li>
			<li><strong>Soft Skills:</strong> Teamwork, Scientific Communication, Creative Problem-Solving</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
</section>

<style>
	.skills-list {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.75rem;
	}
	.skills-list li {
		background: var(--gray-900);
		padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
		border-radius: 0.75rem;
		box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
	}
	.skills-list strong {
		color: var(--gray-0);
	}
</style>

		</main>

		<ContactCTA />
	</div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.about {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 3.5rem;
	}

	img {
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
		border-radius: 1.5rem;
		box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
	}

	section {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.5rem;
		color: var(--gray-200);
	}

	.section-title {
		grid-column-start: 1;
		font-size: var(--text-xl);
		color: var(--gray-0);
	}

	.content {
		grid-column: 2 / 4;
	}

	.content :global(a) {
		text-decoration: 1px solid underline transparent;
		text-underline-offset: 0.25em;
		transition: text-decoration-color var(--theme-transition);
	}

	.content :global(a:hover),
	.content :global(a:focus) {
		text-decoration-color: currentColor;
	}

	@media (min-width: 50em) {
		.about {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: 1fr 60% 1fr;
		}

		.about > :global(:first-child) {
			grid-column-start: 2;
		}

		section {
			display: contents;
			font-size: var(--text-lg);
		}
	}
</style>
